Describe a skill that you can teach other people
- what it is
- when you learned it
- how you can teach others
- how you feel about this skill

I’d like to talk about cooking, which is a skill I feel confident teaching to others.

I first learned how to cook when I was in high school. At that time, I often helped my mother prepare meals for the family. She’s a great cook, so I picked up a lot of useful techniques and recipes from her. Over time, cooking became one of my favorite hobbies.

These days, I still cook regularly, especially since I share a room with some friends. I’m usually the one who prepares meals for us, and they often compliment my food, which really motivates me to keep improving. I also like trying out new recipes by watching online tutorials or cooking shows.

If I were to teach someone, I would start with simple dishes and guide them step by step. I think the best way to learn cooking is through practice, so I would encourage them to cook regularly rather than just watch. I’d also share some small tips I’ve learned, like how to balance flavors or prepare ingredients efficiently.

Personally, I feel really positive about this skill because it’s both practical and enjoyable. It allows me to take care of myself and others, and I find it quite relaxing. I also believe cooking is something anyone can learn with enough patience and practice.
